# ── .dockerignore ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file tells Docker which files to EXCLUDE from the build context.
# The "build context" is everything Docker sends to the daemon when you
# run `docker build .` — it defaults to the entire project directory.
#
# Without this file, `COPY . .` in the Dockerfile would include:
#   - .venv/           (hundreds of MB, unnecessary — pip installs in the image)
#   - data/            (GBs of PDFs and processed artifacts — go on S3, not the image)
#   - .env             (your secrets — NEVER put these in a Docker image)
#   - .paddlex/        (old Paddle cache in CWD — not needed in the image)
#   - __pycache__/     (compiled bytecodes for YOUR machine's Python — not portable)
#
# HOW IT WORKS: Same syntax as .gitignore. Each line is a glob pattern.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Version control ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.gitignore

# ── Python virtual environments ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# The Dockerfile creates its own environment via pip install.
# Your local .venv must NOT be copied — it is built for your OS, not the
# container's Linux environment, and would override the container's packages.
.venv/
venv/

# ── Python bytecache ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# ── Local environment / secrets ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# CRITICAL: Never include .env in a Docker image.
# API keys baked into images can be extracted by anyone with image access.
# Instead, inject secrets at runtime via ECS Secrets Manager or docker-compose env_file.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ── Large data directories ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These directories hold GBs of data that:
#   - Should not be in the image (makes it huge)
#   - Change at runtime (documents processed during operation)
#   - Are persisted in S3 (for AWS) or a Docker volume (for local dev)
data/raw/
data/processed/
data/embedded/
data/.paddlex_cache/

# Old capitalized Data/ directory
Data/

# Old local Paddle cache
.paddlex/

# ── Tests ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tests are for development only — not needed in the production image.
tests/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
coverage.xml

# ── Documentation ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.md
!requirements.txt

# ── Infrastructure files ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Terraform and CI/CD files have no place inside the runtime container.
# scripts/download_models.py is intentionally NOT excluded — it is needed
# by Stage 3 of the Dockerfile to pre-download Paddle models.
infra/
.github/

# ── IDE and OS metadata ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# ── Claude Code worktree metadata ────────────────────────────────────────────
.claude/
